## FF should not be synthesized when black boxes are present

Signal edge of "RESET" used in condition of if statement does not match that specified in the sensitivity list of always block
```verilog
module TOP (OUT_CLK, IN, CLK, SET, RESET);
  input IN, CLK, SET, RESET;
  output OUT_CLK;

  reg OUT_CLK;
  always@(posedge CLK or negedge SET or negedge RESET) begin
    if (!SET)
      OUT_CLK <= 1'b1;
    else if (RESET)   // violation
      OUT_CLK <= 1'b0;
    else
      OUT_CLK <= IN;
      end
endmodule
```
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60563693/155289811-b214d118-978b-425b-b921-d24a2eface1e.png)

I'm not very sure if this is a bug?

Looking forward to your reply

Thanks

